< 15, the Pop III.1 stars are formed in relatively cool gas\nclouds due to efficient radiative cooling by H_2 and HD molecules; such stars\nhave masses of a few x 10 Msun. Since the stellar evolution and the final fate\nare determined by the stellar mass, Pop III stars formed at different epochs\nplay different roles in the early universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Jan 2015 21:00:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 7 Feb 2015 10:09:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-10"}
